Tie-StorableDir version 0.06
============================

Tie::StorableDir is a module which ties a hash to a backing directory. It uses
Storable.pm to serialize and deserialize perl data structures, and escapes keys
so reserved characters may be used.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Build.PL
   ./Build
   ./Build test
   ./Build install

DEPENDENCIES

This module requires these other modules and libraries:

  * IO::Dir
  * Storable
  * Perl 5.8.0 or greater

